I"\<p>Cablegram 55 NANKING, 3 February 1949, 4.25 p.m.</p>

<p>IMMEDIATE TOP SECRET</p>

<p>My telegram 53. [1] The Vice-Minister for Foreign Affairs [2] has advised that the Acting President is most anxious that you should make a statement, on the lines indicated, at a very early date.</p>

<p>2. Therefore, I repeat my proposal in paragraph (2) of the abovementioned telegram regarding 9th February. Broadcast could point out your position as President of the United Nations Assembly.</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 Document 239 2 George K.C. Yeh.</p>

<p>_</p>

